    "In the future, we will introduce more powerful backbone like Transformer into CSVR to further explore potential of the learning framework for various video understanding tasks.",
    "We hope our CSVR can inspire the researches on the collaboration of discriminative and generative self-supervised learning.Fig. 1:1Video Generating Branch Fig.",
    "2: Detailed structure of integration layer.",
    "In the process of generating the integrated feature f i, we use the parameters generated from f d to denormalize the normalized fs, and combine the denormalized feature D and static context feature f s with the an attention mask M. Fig. 3: 50 70Fig.",
    "4:3504 Fig. 3: Action recognition results on UCF101 with different combinations of σ p, σ c. Hyperparameter Investigation of σ p, σ c. CSVR contains three branches which are jointly optimized by loss function L. σ p, σ c in L are the hyperparameters that coordinate the weights Although we use the off-the-shelf pose estimator OpenPose, which is trained with pose supervision, we provide no additional supervision for the action recognition tasks."
